WEBVTT

01:54.201 --> 01:55.289
- We're under attack!

02:01.860 --> 02:03.732
- Run, run, run, run!

02:03.775 --> 02:05.908
Come on, Brendan,
get up! Get up!

02:23.926 --> 02:26.668
- Anyone not dead, fall back!

02:26.711 --> 02:28.887
- Quist, come on!

02:28.931 --> 02:30.193
Head for that building!

02:30.237 --> 02:32.369
Run, run, run!

02:32.413 --> 02:33.979
Move it!

02:38.027 --> 02:39.289
- MAN: Move, move, move!

02:41.987 --> 02:43.859
- Clear!

02:43.902 --> 02:45.469
- Doc, Rivers,
cover those windows.

02:47.645 --> 02:49.691
Quist, cover our tail with Doc.

02:51.562 --> 02:53.129
- Stay low.
Watch for a second wave.

02:57.873 --> 02:59.179
- Doc, anyone out there?

03:01.311 --> 03:03.008
- Negative. Nothing moving
over here.

03:05.620 --> 03:07.491
- Looks like we lost 'em.

03:07.535 --> 03:08.840
Stay sharp, people.

03:15.195 --> 03:17.240
- Cap, what about
Glenn and Denards?

03:17.284 --> 03:19.416
Shouldn't we go back?
Or at least--

03:19.460 --> 03:21.592
- CAPTAIN: Glenn and
Denards are dead, Rivers.

03:21.636 --> 03:24.073
We're all that's left
of B Company.

03:24.116 --> 03:25.422
We're on our own.

03:25.466 --> 03:26.728
- Tell you what.

03:26.771 --> 03:28.251
This whole freaking mission
has been

03:28.295 --> 03:30.297
a goddamn shit sandwich
since Normandy.

03:30.340 --> 03:32.081
We got Krauts to the left.

03:32.124 --> 03:33.604
Freaking minefields
to the right.

03:33.648 --> 03:35.215
How you gonna get us
out of this one, Talby?

03:35.258 --> 03:37.304
- Captain Talby.
- Whatever, wiseass.

03:37.347 --> 03:39.436
- I'm thinking about it.
- Really?

03:39.480 --> 03:42.091
That makes me feel a whole
lot better...Captain.

03:47.618 --> 03:50.447
What the hell is this
place supposed to be anyway?

03:50.491 --> 03:52.667
- It appears to have been
a local police station.

03:56.105 --> 03:58.934
- Looks like they
had some trouble, too.

03:58.977 --> 04:00.892
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

04:10.598 --> 04:11.599
- What the fuck happened here?

04:11.642 --> 04:14.123
Jesus.

04:15.124 --> 04:17.605
- Ooh!

04:17.648 --> 04:19.520
Dear God.

04:19.563 --> 04:21.348
Hey, we got a man down.

04:21.391 --> 04:23.437
We got a couple of 'em.

04:23.480 --> 04:25.961
Oh, would you look at
this shit on my boot, man?

04:29.486 --> 04:32.620
So sorry, sir.
I'm so sorry. I just--

04:32.663 --> 04:34.274
- You goddamn baby.

04:34.317 --> 04:35.492
What the fuck's
the matter with you?

04:35.536 --> 04:37.494
- Leave him be, Quist.

04:37.538 --> 04:39.670
- This piss tank just
yacked all over my foot.

04:39.714 --> 04:40.889
- And I said leave him be.

04:40.932 --> 04:43.065
Stop being an asshole
for two seconds.

04:43.108 --> 04:44.458
- Oh, I'm being the asshole?

04:44.501 --> 04:46.198
- No, Bugs Bunny's the asshole.

04:46.242 --> 04:48.026
Of course you are.

04:48.070 --> 04:50.246
- Gentlemen, this is the last
thing we need right now.

04:56.426 --> 04:58.385
- Hail Mary full of grace.

04:59.995 --> 05:00.952
- What happened here?

05:02.302 --> 05:03.520
- Captain, his
throat's slashed.

05:03.564 --> 05:04.782
He can't talk.

05:10.005 --> 05:11.354
- He's dead.

05:14.270 --> 05:15.619
- Boo fucking hoo.

05:15.663 --> 05:18.318
Hey, Rivers, you wanna
light a candle for him?

06:03.450 --> 06:07.236
-  Hans.

06:07.279 --> 06:11.327
You foolish, foolish boy.

06:14.504 --> 06:19.161
How could my...only son...

06:19.204 --> 06:20.075
allow this?

06:23.774 --> 06:28.823
You have dishonored
the Schmelzgerat name.

06:32.827 --> 06:37.397
But I will find
these American dogs

06:37.440 --> 06:40.487
responsible for this.

06:40.530 --> 06:43.141
And they--

06:43.185 --> 06:48.364
they will suffer...greatly.

06:54.631 --> 06:56.807
- Sir?

06:56.851 --> 06:58.243
What are we gonna do?

07:02.987 --> 07:04.641
- We got a map here.

07:04.685 --> 07:07.470
- Hail Mary full of grace,
the Lord is with thee.

07:07.514 --> 07:08.993
Bless--

07:09.037 --> 07:11.822
- Village of
10 kilometers.

07:11.866 --> 07:13.258
- We're near Le Monge.

07:13.302 --> 07:16.000
- Yeah, yeah, yeah,
hey, that's our rally point.

07:16.044 --> 07:18.394
Alright, we make it there, our
asses our saved. We gotta go.

07:18.438 --> 07:20.527
- Hell ya.
Prepare to move out.

07:20.570 --> 07:21.745
- WOMAN:

07:21.789 --> 07:23.921
- Jesus!

07:30.493 --> 07:32.147
- Jesus, man.

07:32.190 --> 07:33.844
- You shot a civilian, Rivers.

07:33.888 --> 07:34.976
- She grabbed me.

07:35.019 --> 07:36.499
I didn't know
anybody was in there.

07:40.242 --> 07:42.287
- I'm--I'm so sorry, ma'am.

07:42.331 --> 07:44.725
I didn't mean--

07:47.728 --> 07:49.556
- Captain, she'll bleed out
if I don't get in there soon.

07:49.599 --> 07:51.296
- Find the keys. They must be
around here somewhere.

07:51.340 --> 07:53.516
- Whoa, whoa, whoa,
Cap, Cap, listen to me.

07:53.560 --> 07:55.953
Every goddamn wienerschnitzel
in this whole goddamn

07:55.997 --> 07:57.389
German army
would have heard that shot.

07:57.433 --> 07:59.000
- Ah!
- We gotta am-scray now.

07:59.043 --> 08:01.263
- You wanna get out
of here, find the keys.

08:01.306 --> 08:02.307
- I can't find them.

08:02.351 --> 08:04.048
I--I'm sorry.

08:04.092 --> 08:05.180
I'm sorry.

08:05.223 --> 08:08.923
- Sorry.

08:08.966 --> 08:10.228
They're in the jail!

08:10.272 --> 08:12.404
- Oh my God.

08:12.448 --> 08:15.277
- Get those keys, Rivers.

08:15.320 --> 08:16.931
- I can't. They're too far.

08:16.974 --> 08:18.019
- Here.

08:20.021 --> 08:21.762
Snag 'em with this.

08:21.805 --> 08:23.720
- WOMAN:

08:23.764 --> 08:25.069
- Listen, Talby.

08:25.113 --> 08:26.549
Listen to me, we're good
as dead if we stay here,

08:26.593 --> 08:27.768
and you know it.

08:27.811 --> 08:30.292
- WOMAN:

08:30.335 --> 08:32.120
- Button your lip, Sergeant,
or I'll button it for real.

08:36.820 --> 08:41.912
- WOMAN:

08:41.956 --> 08:42.826
- I got 'em!

08:42.870 --> 08:43.958
I got 'em!

08:48.223 --> 08:50.007
No!

08:50.051 --> 08:53.097
- No! no! No!
- It's okay.

08:53.141 --> 08:54.577
- Help me hold her down!

08:54.621 --> 08:58.929
- WOMAN:

09:05.893 --> 09:07.111
- Christ, she's strong.

09:07.155 --> 09:08.199
Doc, what is she saying?

09:08.243 --> 09:09.723
- "Don't kill me.
Go away, I think."

09:12.464 --> 09:14.902
- She might also be saying,
"Go away or I'll kill you."

09:14.945 --> 09:16.686
- Kill us?
- This is crazy, man.

09:16.730 --> 09:18.209
She's gonna give
away our position.

09:19.820 --> 09:22.692
- Fuck this!

09:22.736 --> 09:24.172
- Quist, put that gun away!

09:24.215 --> 09:25.826
- I don't think so, Tommy.

09:25.869 --> 09:28.393
Either way I'm getting
killed over some fog bitch.

09:28.437 --> 09:29.873
- No!

09:34.965 --> 09:38.839
- Ah!

09:41.668 --> 09:44.366
You guys are all a bunch
of goddamn lunatics!

09:44.409 --> 09:46.629
- What happened to you, Quist?

09:46.673 --> 09:48.326
You used to be
someone I could trust.

09:51.634 --> 09:53.244
War changes a man.

09:53.288 --> 09:54.463
- Bastard!

09:54.506 --> 09:55.986
- Sorry, boys.

09:56.030 --> 09:57.118
- Come back here, Quist!

09:57.161 --> 10:00.034
- Can't risk a bullet
in the back.

10:00.077 --> 10:02.471
- Quist!

10:02.514 --> 10:04.081
Quist!

10:07.389 --> 10:08.564
- CAPTAIN:  Quist!

10:17.617 --> 10:18.879
Shit!

10:18.922 --> 10:20.489
- Captain, what
are we gonna do?

10:24.014 --> 10:27.365
- I'll get us out of here,
Rivers, come hell or high water.

10:27.409 --> 10:28.410
I promise.

10:28.453 --> 10:30.673
- Captain, come here.

10:30.717 --> 10:32.153
- She not gonna make it, Doc?

10:45.732 --> 10:47.037
- My God.

10:49.431 --> 10:51.302
What are you?

10:54.044 --> 10:56.220
- "I locked myself
in this cage."

10:58.875 --> 11:00.442
- I cannot die.

11:05.447 --> 11:07.667
- The curse make me
do so many bad things.

11:12.584 --> 11:13.977
- I kill people.

11:15.587 --> 11:17.154
- Kill--

11:18.242 --> 11:20.244
- --children.

11:21.245 --> 11:22.682
- No more death.

11:22.725 --> 11:24.335
- No more killing.

11:27.338 --> 11:28.513
- Please just let me die.

11:34.258 --> 11:35.738
- Loup garou!

11:35.782 --> 11:37.174
- Lugaroo?

11:37.218 --> 11:38.959
- Loup garou.

11:39.002 --> 11:42.527
It means...wolf man.

11:42.571 --> 11:44.094
- Or wolf woman.

11:53.538 --> 11:55.236
- She wasn't trying
to grab me before.

11:58.021 --> 11:59.240
She wanted my cross.

12:02.417 --> 12:05.202
- "Please just let me die."

12:05.246 --> 12:06.638
- It's silver.

12:14.124 --> 12:16.126
- MAN ON LOUDSPEAKER:
Attention, American soldiers!

12:16.170 --> 12:17.824
We know you are inside.

12:17.867 --> 12:19.739
My men have
the building surrounded.

12:19.782 --> 12:20.740
- Perfect timing.

12:24.221 --> 12:28.791
- I will be, as you Americans
like to say, to the point.

12:28.835 --> 12:33.143
One of you...killed...

12:33.187 --> 12:35.755
my only son today,

12:35.798 --> 12:41.151
who causes all of you will die!

12:41.195 --> 12:45.634
But I am a man of honor,
and so I offer you a choice.

12:45.677 --> 12:51.335
If...you come out now
unarmed and accept your fate,

12:51.379 --> 12:54.686
your death will be
quick and painless.

12:54.730 --> 12:59.343
But if you force me
to risk the lives of my men...

12:59.387 --> 13:03.565
to expel your filthy hides...

13:03.608 --> 13:08.091
you will die in unimaginable...

13:08.135 --> 13:10.572
agony.

13:10.615 --> 13:13.009
I await your response.

13:13.053 --> 13:14.619
- Damn.

13:35.727 --> 13:39.253
- Here, ma'am, take it.

13:39.296 --> 13:40.994
It'll do you more
good than it did us.

13:47.739 --> 13:49.002
- Hold up.

13:54.921 --> 13:58.925
- But before you die, we need
you to do something for us.

14:05.540 --> 14:07.281
- This is
Captain Lawrence Talby

14:07.324 --> 14:09.109
of the United Stated Army.

14:09.152 --> 14:10.893
And I've considered your offer.

14:10.937 --> 14:12.199
- What is your answer,

14:12.242 --> 14:15.811
Captain Talby
of the United States Army?

14:15.855 --> 14:17.421
- CAPTAIN: Let me
be to the point!

14:18.901 --> 14:22.296
If you want our filthy hides...

14:22.339 --> 14:25.865
come in here and get 'em!

14:25.908 --> 14:27.518
- Good.

14:27.562 --> 14:30.260
That is good.

14:30.304 --> 14:31.435
We are going in.

14:31.479 --> 14:34.264
Attack at sundown.

14:34.308 --> 14:35.439
- Hurry, let her do it.

14:41.054 --> 14:43.056
- Deploy smoke grenades.

14:59.028 --> 15:00.203
- Thank you.

15:00.247 --> 15:01.857
You...

15:10.779 --> 15:12.781
-  I don't feel
any different.

15:12.824 --> 15:15.001
- What if it ain't
gonna work on us?

15:15.044 --> 15:16.654
- Captain?

15:16.698 --> 15:17.960
- Captain?

15:19.135 --> 15:21.094
- I promised I'd get
you out of here.

15:25.141 --> 15:28.579
Come hell or high water.

16:13.407 --> 16:15.931
- My God, wolf man.

16:19.674 --> 16:20.762
- Fire!

17:05.328 --> 17:07.548
- Ah! Ah! Ah!

17:14.163 --> 17:16.687
- You filthy dog!

18:06.563 --> 18:07.782
- Hello, Sergeant.

18:07.825 --> 18:09.697
- Talby.

18:09.740 --> 18:10.915
- I thought you'd
never wake up.

18:19.359 --> 18:21.361
- Ssshh.

18:24.320 --> 18:26.801
- Doc and Rivers wish they
could've been here, but they're,

18:26.844 --> 18:30.718
um, grabbing a bite to
eat with some Germans.

18:30.761 --> 18:34.809
So it's just you...and me.

18:34.852 --> 18:38.682
-  Talby, I'm
so sorry--I'm so sorry about

18:38.726 --> 18:40.510
what happened back there.

18:40.554 --> 18:42.512
I was scared.

18:42.556 --> 18:44.514
Talby! Talby!

18:44.558 --> 18:47.735
You're--you're--you're
not the kind of guy

18:47.778 --> 18:50.607
that would hurt
a defenseless asshole like me.

18:59.834 --> 19:01.140
- It's like you said, Sergeant.

19:03.011 --> 19:05.753
War changes a man.

20:06.422 --> 20:08.555
- CLARK: My name
is Clark Wilson.

20:08.598 --> 20:11.340
And I gotta say, there's some
pretty weird shit going on.

20:13.864 --> 20:16.824
Now, I usually consider myself
a guy who has his shit together,

20:16.867 --> 20:21.742
because most of the time,
well--I'll get into that later.

20:21.785 --> 20:24.832
But in this case, this is all
a bit out of the ordinary,

20:24.875 --> 20:27.791
I gotta say.

20:27.835 --> 20:29.271
I can hear you.

20:38.454 --> 20:39.890
I got a big fucking gun here!

21:00.346 --> 21:01.912
But I don't want
to get too ahead of myself,

21:01.956 --> 21:03.392
so let me start over.

21:05.873 --> 21:08.179
You know how they say
nobody walks in L.A.?

21:08.223 --> 21:11.182
Well, I'm the guy
who walks in L.A.

21:11.226 --> 21:13.881
Like I said before, my
name is Clark Wilson.

21:13.924 --> 21:17.319
I have what you might call
a passion for found objects.

21:17.363 --> 21:19.800
You know, everyday things that
have been lost, thrown away,

21:19.843 --> 21:21.932
or abandoned.

21:21.976 --> 21:23.282
Take this lock for instance.

21:25.414 --> 21:27.808
This used to be new once.

21:27.851 --> 21:29.288
It had a purpose.

21:29.331 --> 21:31.028
It was useful once.

21:31.072 --> 21:33.683
And now it's been forsaken.

21:33.727 --> 21:35.337
Kinda like me, if you
wanna get right down to it.

21:39.515 --> 21:41.691
Now, I had this friend
once who had this dog.

21:41.735 --> 21:44.607
Now, he claimed that if you fed
this dog some weed

21:44.651 --> 21:45.782
in a rolling paper,

21:45.826 --> 21:47.828
it would poop out
a perfectly rolled joint.

21:47.871 --> 21:50.526
Now, I never saw the dog do it.

21:50.570 --> 21:52.659
And I never really
believed that story.

21:52.702 --> 21:56.227
But...actually,
come to think of it,

21:56.271 --> 21:58.142
you're probably not gonna
believe this story either.

22:14.594 --> 22:15.856
- CLARK: The last thing
I expected that night

22:15.899 --> 22:18.337
was to get
the finger...for real.

22:20.426 --> 22:23.429
It was verification that the
whole world was flipping me off.

22:23.472 --> 22:25.909
"Hey, fuck you, loser."

22:25.953 --> 22:29.130
Or maybe...just maybe,

22:29.173 --> 22:31.741
it was the other way around.

22:31.785 --> 22:34.614
I guess I'm just your average,
ordinary, so-called citizen.

22:34.657 --> 22:35.702
Mortgage sucks.

22:35.745 --> 22:37.573
Job prospects suck.

22:37.617 --> 22:39.836
Abandoned by my so-called
family three years ago.

22:45.451 --> 22:49.368
Anyway, I got this house
when Samantha divorced me.

22:49.411 --> 22:51.021
I got the crap house,
the shit mortgage,

22:51.065 --> 22:52.762
the lamentable car,

22:52.806 --> 22:55.112
and a career in web design.

22:55.156 --> 22:58.159
Which is a cute way of saying
I'm mostly unemployed.

22:58.202 --> 22:59.378
I hang on.

22:59.421 --> 23:00.596
I telecommute.

23:00.640 --> 23:02.337
Well, that's what I tell people.

23:02.381 --> 23:05.601
I tell them I
tele--you know what?

23:05.645 --> 23:06.776
Never mind.

23:12.173 --> 23:14.218
Armadillo? No.

23:14.262 --> 23:15.655
Raccoon?

23:15.698 --> 23:16.830
No.

23:16.873 --> 23:19.441
Is it a possum?

23:19.485 --> 23:20.877
Uh, no.

23:20.921 --> 23:23.053
- Fuck!

23:23.097 --> 23:26.666
Ugh! Goddamn it.

23:33.890 --> 23:35.588
- Wow.

23:35.631 --> 23:36.502
That's noteworthy.

23:39.330 --> 23:42.333
You, my friend, are a keeper.

24:01.527 --> 24:03.311
- WOMAN ON PHONE: This is
a call from a debt collector.

24:03.354 --> 24:05.313
This call may be recorded
for quality assurance.

24:05.356 --> 24:07.097
Your account is important to us.

24:07.141 --> 24:08.664
- Why don't you
just fucking die?

24:08.708 --> 24:11.667
Die, die, die,
you fucking vampires!

24:16.193 --> 24:18.065
Sorry.

24:18.108 --> 24:21.416
I'm not normally
this...um, agro.

24:21.460 --> 24:24.375
It's just--I mean, come on.

24:24.419 --> 24:25.899
You hate them, too, right?

24:25.942 --> 24:28.075
Those anonymous people,
who aren't even really people.

24:30.817 --> 24:33.994
Don't you just wish you
could make them suffer?

24:34.037 --> 24:35.865
Suffer the way they've
made you suffer?

24:37.650 --> 24:40.827
Anyway, the instant
family from hell, right?

24:43.220 --> 24:45.832
Had reached its sell-by date.

24:45.875 --> 24:48.095
Samantha eventually needed
someone who could do more

24:48.138 --> 24:51.402
than get things off
a high shelf,

24:51.446 --> 24:53.317
fetch her tampons,

24:53.361 --> 24:54.667
run out to the store at 3:00AM

24:54.710 --> 24:57.713
to buy those pretentious
little cigarettes.

24:57.757 --> 25:01.891
Her idiot son, Ricky, stole
my car and tried to hock it.

25:01.935 --> 25:04.111
Her daughter once offered me
a blowjob to keep quiet

25:04.154 --> 25:06.069
about her meth habit
and the fact that

25:06.113 --> 25:09.377
her latest fiancÃ©e
was doing time for murder.

25:09.420 --> 25:13.381
But, hey, it's
the American dream, right?

25:13.424 --> 25:15.731
Domestic bliss.

25:15.775 --> 25:18.821
Sam used to say, "It's the way
it's supposed to be."

25:21.432 --> 25:22.433
No, it's not.

25:22.477 --> 25:24.392
Blogs? Seriously?

25:24.435 --> 25:26.699
What year is this, Blurserno?
2006?

25:26.742 --> 25:28.265
- BLURSERNO ON PHONE:
They're clients, Clark.

25:28.309 --> 25:29.963
They're digitally challenged.

25:30.006 --> 25:31.704
It's work, for fuck's sake.

25:31.747 --> 25:33.053
- It's donkey work.

25:33.096 --> 25:34.620
I'm not doing it.

25:34.663 --> 25:37.971
- BLURSERNO ON PHONE:
It's donkey work that pays.

25:38.014 --> 25:39.189
- Let me call you back.

25:48.242 --> 25:49.373
- Goddamn it.

26:06.956 --> 26:08.479
- Holy hell.

26:25.932 --> 26:29.892
- CLARK: And within 24 hours,
I had myself a whole arm.

26:29.936 --> 26:31.459
The suspense was killing me.

26:33.200 --> 26:35.028
I'm beginning to think maybe
I need to call a grownup.

26:37.683 --> 26:39.075
What would an adult do?

26:52.306 --> 26:54.134
- Maybe I should call a museum.

26:54.177 --> 26:55.875
Or a mad scientist.

26:55.918 --> 26:58.921
Or maybe, just maybe...

26:58.965 --> 27:01.445
I can wait
a little while longer.

27:30.649 --> 27:33.173
- CLARK: This wasn't like
misplacing a set of keys.

27:33.216 --> 27:35.523
This was the first time
something I had salvaged,

27:35.566 --> 27:38.004
something I had
saved...

27:38.047 --> 27:39.440
abandoned me.

27:55.151 --> 27:56.587
